cs.MS, cs.CE, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, q-bio.SC

The paper discusses a hybrid modeling approach to cell cycle regulation, which involves both continuous and discrete changes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.MS (Mathematical Software) which deals with the development and use of mathematical models and software tools for simulation and analysis of complex systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of learning strategies for the parameters of the hybrid model, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) which deals with the development and application of computational methods in various fields. Finally, the paper also discusses the spatio-temporal re-organisation of the cell and the rapid changes of regulatory proteins concentrations induced by post-translational modifications, which are relevant to the sub-categories of q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) and q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs) that deal with the quantitative analysis of biological systems and the modeling of tissues and organs. The paper could also belong to the sub-category of q-bio.SC (Subcellular Processes) which deals with the study of biological processes at the subcellular level.
